Subject: Re: [T2] Emissions parts vs. non-Emissions


> I have a '78 camper and was wondering what was added to California models
> for emissions control.  I've seen a part for a catalytic converter and I've
> heard that the gas tank is different.
>
> Two questions:
>
> 1) Can the converter be bolted onto the non-emissions exhaust?

Yes, it takes the place of the straight pipe between the U pipe and the muffler.
Ron at Bus Depot has a drawing of it:
http://www.busdepot.com/partsimages/exhaust27578.JPG
You should have #5. The cat takes it's place.

> 2) What's different about the gas tank?

The filler neck has a 'fillpipe restricter' built into it so you can only use a
smaller unleaded nozzle.


